The paper focuses on video captioning, which involves analyzing and generating natural language descriptions of videos. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of multi-modal features, which involves combining information from different modalities such as image, scene, action, and audio. This is a common theme in multimedia analysis (cs.MM). The paper also compares different encoder-decoder models and explores how different features affect the quality of generated statements, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
